<p>Growing up is like making a tie-dye T-shirt: twisting, turning, tying, and coloring experimentally with loose yet hopeful expectations of what the permanent results of our decisions will look like.</p><p>In this blur of figuring out ourselves and prodding at our identity &#8212; a journey that is usually done alone &#8212; we learn to <em>be</em> ourselves. The hallmark of artistic maturity is the ability to transform that elemental loneliness into the <a href="https://www.theplurisociety.com/p/the-joy-of-being-alone-and-bored">&#8220;fertile solitude&#8221;</a> psychoanalyst Adam Philips called the elixir of our creativity, the &#8220;fruitful monotony&#8221; Bertrand Russell recognized as the key to our happiness.</p><p>And when we&#8217;re inspired enough, we reach out from this primal loneliness to other lonelinesses in that great gesture of connection we call art.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1954eef-e08a-46f3-9ec2-ce60a74f0c21_1109x640.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1954eef-e08a-46f3-9ec2-ce60a74f0c21_1109x640.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1954eef-e08a-46f3-9ec2-ce60a74f0c21_1109x640.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1954eef-e08a-46f3-9ec2-ce60a74f0c21_1109x640.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_14